// Components used are
Hardware and Modules Used

LCD Display (I2C-based, e.g., 16x2 LCD)
HX711 Module (Analog-to-Digital Converter for load cell)
Load Cell (Weight measurement sensor)
GSM Module (e.g., SIM800L, for sending SMS notifications)
Arduino Microcontroller (e.g., Arduino Uno or Nano)
LEDs (For status or alert indicators)
Resistors (For circuit connections)
Jumper Wires (For making electrical connections)
Breadboard or PCB (For circuit assembly)
Power Supply (USB cable, battery, or external adapter)



// Software used

Arduino IDE (for programming the Arduino microcontroller)
Serial Monitor (for debugging and monitoring output)
Libraries:
LiquidCrystal_I2C (for LCD control)
HX711 Library (for load cell integration)

